ices, spaces, temporalities and imaginaries cross-cutting throughout. In doing so, it draws on the work of a range of established and up-and-coming scholars researching the everyday, including human geographers, sociologists, anthropologists, urban planners, cartographers, and fashion historians. With empirical examples, practical tips, ethical considerations, and exercises.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHuman behavior. 0aSociologyxResearch. 4aManchester Digital Textbooks. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Research.2bisacsh  aEmotions.  aEveryday life.  aInnovation.  aMateriality.  aMemory.  aMobility.  aMundane.  aQualitative.  aResearch methods.  aSenses.1 aBack, Les, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirtchnell, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlake, Megan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChapman, Lynne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollins, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Sarah Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Sarah Marie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarada, Theresa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeath, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Helen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLyon, Dawn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLean, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.